Gilman’s conceit was a metaphor for the ways in which the domestic sphere can often double as a prison for women.
We’re all living in “The Yellow Wallpaper” now.
So, too, is it a privilege to have living quarters with sufficient space for practicing social distancing, or indeed to have a roof over our heads at all.
But none of this means that staying home all the time, day after day, is easy for any of us.
There are times when it’s acceptable to leave the house and times when the social imperative is to stay inside.